law.history: Repealed 1982 Ky. Acts ch. 393, sec. 51, effective July 15, 1982. -- Amended 1974 Ky. Acts ch. 74, Art. VI, sec. 107(27). -- Created 1948 Ky. Acts ch. 236, secs. 1, 2, and 3.

metadata.catchline-at-repeal: Social security appropriations not to lapse at end of first fiscal year of biennium.
metadata.note: 1948 Ky. Acts ch. 236 created three new sections of the statutes, reading exactly the same, to be numbered KRS 200.045, 205.045, and 207.085. These three sections were consolidated into one, and codified as KRS 45.235, effective 1948.
